9:{i:0;s:45:"Herein why would my garage door stop working.";i:1;s:103:"When the garage door opener does not work with either the remote or the wall switch look at the lights.";i:2;s:49:"If theyre not on the unit is not receiving power.";i:3;s:145:"Pull the chain to disengage the carriage and allow the garage door to function independently of the openerThen attempt to open the door manually.";i:4;s:117:"Another reason that your garage door wont open all the way in cold weather is probably that the metal has contracted.";i:5;s:81:"In cold temperature the space between molecules reduces making the metal shrinks.";i:6;s:97:"If this is the reason your garage door is not functioning properly the lubricant must be applied.";i:7;s:87:"Lubricating the springs hinges and other metal parts can help your door to move easily.";i:8;s:33:"There are a few possible answers.";i:9;s:90:"If a garage door opens on its own and doesnt obey your commands here are some reasons why.";i:10;s:91:"Photo-eye sensors are quite reliable but also responsive to any type of debris or blockage.";i:11;s:94:"If your garage door randomly opens midway check whether the sensor itself is dirty or smudged.";i:12;s:105:"According to a persistent urban legend a plane passing over your home can cause your garage door to open.";i:13;s:119:"To correct many peoples misimpression we should point out that it all depends on the frequency used by the door opener.";i:14;s:40:"The frequency used in older garage door.";i:15;s:70:"Your garage doors logic board is the brain of your garage door opener.";i:16;s:64:"This brain can wear out in time so you could need a replacement.";i:17;s:115:"When the logic board wears out it can cause your garage door to close then open and vice versa without explanation.";i:18;s:28:"Get Logic Board Replacement.";i:19;s:78:"A faulty logic board could also be a reason your garage door opens then stops.";i:20;s:81:"This board electrically controls your garage door and will fail if it shorts ou